{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"round cake tin (20 cm), baking paper, serving plate, wooden skewer, oven","id":"r125903","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/--GTzYj1S_Y4\/XZWpqWYGxRI\/AAAAAAAAfNM\/wrFfPe9b5eMTULtLxwYtckdMUPaf_kHtgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1pMEg_fbPpu9eHn8.png","title":"Peach and plum upside-down cake","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"100 g extra virgin coconut oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"¼ tsp grated nutmeg (optional)"},{"content":"80 g brown sugar, plus extra 2 tsp for sprinkling (see Tips)"},{"content":"2 fresh blood plums (approx. 100 g each), stones removed and cut into 6 or 8 wedges"},{"content":"2 peaches (approx. 100 g each), stones removed and cut into 6 or 8 wedges"},{"content":"1 - 2 sprigs fresh rosemary, leaves only (approx. 2-3 tsp)"},{"content":"2 eggs"},{"content":"1 tsp natural vanilla extract"},{"content":"100 g milk (see Tips)"},{"content":"200 g wholemeal spelt flour"},{"content":"2 tsp baking powder"},{"content":"½ tsp bicarbonate of soda"},{"content":"Greek natural yoghurt, to serve (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"3.8 g","fat":"9.9 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"22 g","calories":"820 kJ \/ 195 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 150°C. Grease and line a round cake tin (20 cm) with baking paper."},{"content":"Sprinkle nutmeg (optional) and 2 teaspoons of the brown sugar over base of prepared tin. Arrange plum and peach wedges in a circular pattern, alternating colours."},{"content":"Place oil, rosemary and remaining 80 g sugar into mixing bowl and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add eggs, vanilla and milk and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add flour, baking powder and bicarbonate of soda and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>, until combined."},{"content":"Spoon mixture over fruit and smooth surface. Bake for 35-40 minutes (150°C), or until golden and a skewer inserted into the centre of the cake comes out clean. Allow to cool in tin for 5-10 minutes, then turn out onto a serving plate. Serve with yoghurt (optional)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<b><b>To make this recipe dairy free, use almond milk instead of cow’s milk and skip the yoghurt when serving.","You can use your preferred brown sugar in this recipe - either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","50m","12 portions"]}